.header-section
	%h1 Design Craftsman Swap
	%h2 
		Tidbits from my time with Kevin, Michael, and Jen; the designers at 
		%a{:href => "http://www.thinkrelevance.com"} Think Relevance.
	%div
.intro-section
	.inner-container
		%h3 Durham, NC
		%p 
			I hadn't ever been to Durham, had never done a craftsman swap and I really wasn't entirely sure what to expect. All I knew was that I was excited to go and experience life in Durham for a week with Relevance and the amazing 
			%a{:href => "http://thinkrelevance.com/team/members/michael-parenteau"} Michael Parenteau, 
			%a{:href => "http://thinkrelevance.com/team/members/kevin-altman"} Kevin Altman, 
			and 
			%a{:href => "http://thinkrelevance.com/team/members/jen-myers"} Jen Myers.

.blog-snippet
	%p.day September 23rd
	%h3 Arrival in Durham
	%p
		I land in Durham somewhere around 5:00 PM and I find a cab. I think about how nice it is that there's no line, I'm handed a peice of paper with a cab number and tell my driver where I'm going. He's very nice and asks about me; where I'm from, what I'm doing in Durham, the usual. He complains about the traffic. I wonder, "what traffic?", we talk about Chicago for a while and then after about 10 minutes, we reach the hotel.
	%p
		I'm really tired from the flight, but hungry. I wonder if I should order room service or just go walk around downtown Durham and try to find something. From looking out my hotel window, I see no one is out, so food doesn't look too promising, but I go out anyway, opting for the adventure instead of hiding in my room.
	%p
		I wander the downtown area for a while. A couple places are open, most are closed. This must be how it is on Sunday nights. I go a different direction for a while and finally there are people. I also see food trucks, which is a lovely surprise. I find out that the area is a park and there is an Obama campaign party happening. I get in line for a sandwich at American Meltdown, eat on a park bench while listening to a band play, then walk back to the hotel enjoying the gorgeous weather.

