.blog-snippet
	%p.day September 26th
	%h3 Day Three at Relevance
	%p
		After the much appreciated ritual of coffee and standup, I worked with Michael for a little while and then spent most of the day working with Kevin. We began brainstorming on the whiteboard, sketching with Balsamiq, and asking Ben more questions in order to gather the information we needed to work on wireframes.
	%p
		Some projects are just so complex and interesting that when you think you have the answers, you probably don't. It becomes so important to spend extra time figuring out what's needed and what's not. This was one of those projects, and it was so much fun working on a tough problem like this one with Kevin.
	%p
		You learn a lot about a person when working with them all day. I just met Michael and Kevin, but it wasn't very long before I felt like I had known them a long time. Some of us went out for some great mexican food and talked for quite a while out on thier patio.

