.blog-snippet
	%p.day September 28th
	%h3 Day Five at Relevance
	%p
		Fridays at Relevance is free time. Time to learn things that you want to learn and work on open source. I mostly just wanted to see what everyone was working on and help anyone that needed it.
	%p
		Most of us went out for lunch and on our way they showed me American Underground, a huge space for startups to work. Each of the glass walled offices had their own style and the names of the companies were projected on the floor of the hallway that we walked through. There was also a small arcade with free games to play so we stopped there for a few minutes. When we got outside where the restaurant was, I learned a little about the Lucky Strike factory, which is now offices. We talked about all kinds of things and ate amazing food at L'Uva, then went back to the office. 
	%p
		Kevin started working on a infographic poster in illustrator based on the things he had done that week. His Illustrator skills are unbelieveable. I could learn a lot from him. It wasn't long until it was time to head to the airport. Kevin gave me a ride and after checking my bag and going through security, I made it to my gate where there was some karoke going on. Unfortunately no one was volunteering, so if fizzled out pretty quickly. As soon as we began boarding, someone started singing “Leaving on a Jet Plane”.
	%p
		The flight back to Chicago felt long and while I was happy to be going home, I was sad to leave Durham and all the people I had just met. I was super anxious on the plane with my head full of all of the things I had learned that week and all the things I wanted to do when I reached solid ground. 

